Me: *thinks about how many women suffered because of that bloody war and about how women...
body:
Me: *sees a post about Ashara Dayne*

Me: *thinks about how many women suffered because of that bloody war and about how women always suffer because of men wars*

Me: *starts to think about Lyanna being beautiful, willful, full of life and loving beauty and fights*

Me: *thinks that she was stolen by a prince and the war that followed*

Me:

Me: Wait a minute…

Me: Game of Thrones is the fanfic of the aftermath of the Trojan War?

Me:

Me: WTF, how could I be so slow?

tags: this poem reminds me so much of her
summary:
O muse that swayest the sad Northern Song, 
Thy right hand full of smiting and of wrong, 
Thy left hand holding pity; and thy...
text:
O muse that swayest the sad Northern Song,
Thy right hand full of smiting and of wrong,
Thy left hand holding pity; and thy breast
Heaving with hope of that so certain rest:
Thou, with the grey eyes kind and unafraid,
The soft lips trembling not, though they have said
The doom of the World and those that dwell therein.
source: TO THE MUSE OF THE NORTH from Poems By The Way & Love Is Enough, by William Morris

body:
JON ADWD

The light of the half-moon(Dny) turned Vals honey-blond hair a pale silver and left her cheeks as white as snow. She took a deep breath. The air tastes sweet.

DAENERYS AGOT

A blue flower(Jon) grew from a chink in a wall of ice, and filled the air with sweetness

“Love is sweet, dearest Ned, but it cannot change a man’s nature. – Lyanna”
